NUMBER 983
REGION 4
CHANNEL 85
WASTE
NAME Idemmu Ag, Road of the Damned
MONSTER_GROUP 96
*DESCRIPTION_START
Imagine a wasteland of sand melted and twisted by a maniacal glassblower. This is what lies beyond the narrow trail -- a forest of glass shards, cruel barbs and crystal spikes that threaten to impale any who dare to tread beyond the path. The road itself has been cleared of such hazards, and paved with shattered, bleached bones. The Ghoul City hulks, silently, to the north, while the road continues deeper into the chaos southwards.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 984
EXIT N 3214
;
NUMBER 984
REGION 4
CHANNEL 85
WASTE
MONSTER_GROUP 96
NAME Idemmu Ag, Road of the Damned
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The road continues to wind southwards. A shore of black sand spreads out to the east, before a vast body of some viscous, dark-red liquid. The maze of razor-edged glass continues to menace western passage.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 983
EXIT E 985
EXIT S 1431
;
NUMBER 985
REGION 4
CHANNEL 85
WASTE
MONSTER_GROUP 96
NAME Idemmu Ag, Shore
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Uncomfortable heat radiates from a black sooty powder that make up the beach. Waves of blood crash violently upon massive, jagged rocks that litter the surf, and the air is filled with a scent that reminds you of a day-old battlefield. Occassionally something flits in the periphery of your vision, but it swiftly vanishes into a purple mist that boils up from the lake.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 984
EXIT SE 986
;
NUMBER 986
REGION 4
CHANNEL 85
WASTE
MONSTER_GROUP 96
NAME Idemmu Ag, Shore
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A finger of land extends out into the lake at this point, while the coast continues to the northwest and southeast. Occasionally, a red, alien plant pops up from beneath the black sand with a hiss, belches a small quantity of blood and then slowly recedes underground again. The same purple haze obscures vision, so you are unable to see what lies at the end of the peninsula.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NW 985
EXIT E 987
;
VARIABLE WHALELOC
VARIABLE WHALELEV
VARIABLE WHALECHA
;
NUMBER 987
REGION 4
WASTE
CHANNEL 85
MONSTER_GROUP 96
NAME Idemmu Ag, Peninsula
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
From this vantage point, the purple mists subsides somewhat, enabling you to
peer out across the expanse of the lake. At some indeterminable distance at
the other side, a range of mountains stand -- and fall. Peaks are born up
from the ground and then die, as if the geologic cycle of the land were
increased a billion-fold. Yet one mountain, larger and stronger than the
rest, survives and stands tall while its brethren kneel and then crumble
before its might. Thunder echos from the mountains, combining with the
crashing of the blood-waves to form a cacophony of anarchy and destruction.
At the very end of the peninsula is a strange metal structure atop which
is mounted a bell. A chain dangles down from the bell.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 986
ITEM 0 332
;
IFVERB PULL 0
	ECHO ALL The bell makes a single, hollow clang.
	PLREVENT 6
	CONTPLREVENT
	EQUAL DUMMY1 0
	AFFECT 988
	IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 0
		EQUAL DUMMY1 1
	ENDIF
	AFFECT 990
	IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 0
		EQUAL DUMMY1 1
	ENDIF
	IFVAR WHALELOC = 0
		IFVAR WHALELOC = 6
			IFVAR WHALECHA = 1
				IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
					AFFECT 992
					ECHO OTHERS You watch as the skeletal whale slips beneath the waves.
				ENDIF
			ENDIF
		ELSE
			EQUAL DUMMY1 WHALECHA
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
	AFFECT 987
	IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
		ECHO ALL A massive shape heaves up from the blood-lake. After a moment of horror, you realize that you are looking at the skeletal hulk of a whale! The undead leviathen opens its mouth and drops its lower jaw on the beach like some sort of gangplank.
		ROOMCOPY 989
		EQUAL WHALELOC 0
		EQUAL WHALECHA 1
		NEWITEM 1 1919 VAL2=988 ADJ1=163 ADJ2=1392 OPEN
		AFFECT 988
		OPEN 1
		SETITEMVAL 1 2 987
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 988
NAME In the Whale, Jaw
REGION 4
WASTE
CHANNEL 85
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are standing inside the skeletal jaw of a massive whale. It smells of death and decay, and its surface is stained red by the lake of blood. An iron ladder has been nailed into the bone and leads up to a dark hole in its brain-case.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 335 VAL2=990 ADJ1=169
ITEM 1 1919 VAL2=987
;
CEVENT 78 6 990
AFFECT 990
IFVAR WHALELEV ! 0
	ADD WHALELOC WHALELEV
	ECHO ALL You hear the rush of liquid beyond the wall of bone.
	IFVAR WHALELOC < 0
		ECHO ALL Suddenly, the skeletal whale grinds to a halt and the lever snaps back to the 'neutral' position.
		EQUAL WHALELOC 0
		EQUAL WHALELEV 0
	ENDIF
	IFVAR WHALELOC > 6
		ECHO ALL Suddenly, the skeletal whale grinds to a halt and the lever snaps back to the 'neutral' position.
		EQUAL WHALELOC 6
		EQUAL WHALELEV 0
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 990
NAME In the Whale, Skull
REGION 4
CHANNEL 85
INDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The whale's brain-case is illuminated by a sickly green light of indeterminate origin. An iron ladder sprouts from a dark hole in the floor, leading back to the jaw. A few other strange objects are mounted into the surface of the skull:  a rusty chain, a three-position lever and a brass periscope.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 335 VAL2=988 ADJ1=169
ITEM 1 332 ADJ1=272
ITEM 2 641
ITEM 3 1920 ADJ1=32
EQUAL DUMMY1 0
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
	IFVAR WHALECHA ! 1
		ECHO PLAYER A hatch has closed, sealing your exit from the whale's skull.
		CLEARVERB
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL 1
	ECHO ALL %N tugs on the rusty chain.
	IFVAR WHALELEV ! 0
		ECHO PLAYER The chain won't budge.
	ELSE
		EQUAL DUMMY5 0
		IFVAR WHALELOC = 0
			EQUAL DUMMY5 1
		ENDIF
		IFVAR WHALELOC = 6
			EQUAL DUMMY5 1
		ENDIF
		IFVAR DUMMY5 ! 1
			ECHO PLAYER The chain refuses to budge.
		ELSE
			IFVAR WHALECHA = 1
				AFFECT 988
				IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 0
					ECHO OTHERS The whale shudders for a moment.
					AFFECT 990
					ECHO OTHERS The whale shudders for a moment.
				ELSE
					EQUAL WHALECHA 0
					IFVAR WHALELOC = 0
						AFFECT 987
						ECHO OTHERS The skeletal whale submerges beneath the waves of blood!
						ROOMCOPY 991
						REMOVEITEM 1
					ENDIF
					IFVAR WHALELOC = 6
						AFFECT 992
						ECHO OTHERS The skeletal whale submerges beneath the waves of blood!
						ROOMCOPY 994
						REMOVEITEM 1
					ENDIF
					AFFECT 990
					ECHO ALL A hatch suddenly slams shut, sealing your escape from the chamber. A moment later, your feel a brief moment of nausea and a feeling of downward motion. The motion then ceases as suddenly as it began.
				ENDIF
			ELSE
				EQUAL WHALECHA 1
				IFVAR WHALELOC = 0
					AFFECT 987
					ECHO OTHERS A massive shape heaves up from the blood-lake. After a moment of horror, you realize that you are looking at the skeletal hulk of a whale! The undead leviathen opens its mouth and drops its lower jaw on the beach like some sort of gangplank.
					ROOMCOPY 989
					EQUAL WHALECHA 1
					NEWITEM 1 1919 VAL2=988 ADJ1=163 ADJ2=1392 OPEN
					AFFECT 988
					OPEN 1
					SETITEMVAL 1 2 987
					AFFECT 990
				ENDIF
				IFVAR WHALELOC = 6
					AFFECT 992
					ECHO OTHERS A massive shape heaves up from the blood-lake. After a moment of horror, you realize that you are looking at the skeletal hulk of a whale! The undead leviathen opens its mouth and drops its lower jaw on the shore.
					ROOMCOPY 993
					EQUAL WHALECHA 1
					NEWITEM 1 1919 VAL2=988 ADJ1=163 ADJ2=1392 OPEN
					AFFECT 988
					OPEN 1
					SETITEMVAL 1 2 992
					AFFECT 990
				ENDIF
				AFFECT 990
				ECHO ALL You experience a sudden sense of upward momentum. After a moment, the feeling ends and the hatch pops open again.
			ENDIF
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL 2
	IFVAR WHALELEV < 0
		ECHO PLAYER The lever won't pull back any further.
	ELSE
		IFVAR WHALECHA = 0
			ECHO ALL %N pulls back on the lever.
			SUB WHALELEV 1
			EQUAL DUMMY1 1
		ELSE
			ECHO PLAYER Odd. The lever won't budge.
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 2
	IFVAR WHALELEV > 0
		ECHO PLAYER The lever won't push forward any further.
	ELSE
		IFVAR WHALECHA = 0
			ECHO ALL %N pushes the lever forward.
			ADD WHALELEV 1
			EQUAL DUMMY1 1
		ELSE
			ECHO PLAYER Odd. The lever won't budge.
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
	IFVAR WHALELEV < 0
		ECHO ALL The lever is now in the 'reverse' position.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR WHALELEV > 0
		ECHO ALL The lever is now in the 'forward' position.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR WHALELEV = 0
		ECHO ALL The lever is now in the 'neutral' position.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
